// Adversarial: SpeedBoost(1.5) fires once on NodeStart — the bolt receives a permanent
// velocity multiplier from frame 1 of the node. Dense layout means the boosted bolt
// immediately encounters cells and wall reflections at 1.5x base speed. Godmode breaker
// guarantees infinite play so the bolt persists across multiple node transitions. The
// adversarial risk: if NodeStart fires more than once per node (e.g. due to state re-entry
// or restart logic), SpeedBoost stacks to 2.25x then 3.375x and escapes BoltMaxSpeed.
// If the boost is applied before the bolt has a BoundEffects component, the fire()
// call silently drops it and no boost occurs — BoltSpeedAccurate won't fire, but the
// scenario documents expected baseline speed range. 3000 frames is sufficient to clear
// most Dense nodes and verify no double-application on node transitions.
(
    breaker: "godmode",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Perfect(AlwaysPerfect),
    max_frames: 3000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 1024,
    initial_effects: [
        On(target: Bolt, then: [
            When(trigger: NodeStart, then: [
                Do(SpeedBoost(multiplier: 1.5)),
            ]),
        ]),
    ],
)
